TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {7601=ITTA BENA, Miss. – The Jackson State football team struggled through three quarters with a tenacious Mississippi Valley State team, but pulled away in the fourth quarter to earn a 26-17 victory over the Delta Devils Saturday at Rice-Totten Stadium. With the win JSU impoves to a 5-2, 5-0 record. The Tigers remain the only team in the SWAC with an unblemished record in conference play and have tied the programs best start since 1995. Mississippi Valley State falls to a 1-5, 1-3 record. , 9058=Jackson State bounced back, as it would for the entire game, with a scoring drive of its own. Clayton Moore led the Tigers on a four play, 68 yard drive that ended in a 17 yard scoring run by the JSU signal caller to tie the game at 7-7 with 5:43 left in the first. , 9601=Each team scored a TD in the third quarter. Clayton Moore connected with Pendleton for a 45 yard scoring strike, making the score 17-10 with 6:15 left in the quarter. Valley responded as Collins hit Julian Stafford for a 19 yard TD pass at the 3:55 mark, tying the game at 17-17., 9351=At the 11:12 mark in the second quarter Ryan Deising connected on a 34 yard field goal, giving JSU a 10-7 advantage. However, with 24 seconds left in the first half Galon tied the game with a 34 yard field goal of his own. , 8722=After JSU was forced to punt on its first offensive possession of the game, the Delta Devils put the first points on the scoreboard. The Delta Devils capped an eight play, 73 yard drive when Cortez Frizell connected with Jeremy Collins on a 22 yard TD pass to take a 7-0 lead at the 6:52 mark in the first quarter., 8216=With the game tied 17-17 in the fourth quarter, the Tigers took the lead for good when Canard Brown blocked a Cherchen Galon punt in the Valley end zone for a safety making the score 19-17 with 9:49 left in regulation.
